20 years of software & management and I can tell you;
This "argument" never happens with experienced senior devs, it's always "how come you X over Y" or "don't use this instead of that". AI picks, and does as it's told, and if you tell it the wrong thing, you have screwed yourself in the future. "Works Now" has cost SO many companies so much money. *Imagine what'll happen when you don't know why.* Any idiot can make it work Now. Whether it works right, is moot, it's good and getting better.

It's "does it meet all of your business expectations" for years down the road. People are replacing jobs with AI; if you replace people with AI, who will be there to know?

